Don't do it like that, pyspider is not scrapy, you don't have to manage and deduplicate the urls yourself. Just submit the urls via `self.crawl` and pyspider will take care the deduplicate things for you.

```
class Handler(BaseHandler):
    def on_start(self):
        self.crawl(start_url, callback=self.detail_page)

    def detail_page(self, response):
        for each in response.doc('a[href^="http"]').items():
            self.crawl(each.attr.href, callback=self.detail_page)
        return {
            ... # extract information here
        }
```

And don't use class member variables, pyspider is designed as distributed, member variables may not be visitable in other instance.

