@wez According to your comments on the PR #306, we now use the same strategy for pywatchman than for watchman itself.

The strategy is: get rid of GetOverlappedResultEx and implement the same behavior using only CreateEvent, WaitForObjectEx and GetOverlappedResult.

Maintenance effort is therefore minimized and comptability is maximized.

