@tcr3dr  I'm far more interested a property for the "last heartbeat timer value" than the last heartbeat timestamp received. With what we have now I think most users will have to implement their own timer ... which is a bit of a pain.

What I think people will want to do is monitor the timeout timer value and in the callback do something when it reaches a particular value. 

The difficult bit is deciding what is a reasonable update period on the timer. I think we want it to update when the value is set to zero. We also want it to update at least once every second. The question is, whether a more frequent period (tenth of second? would ever be useful).

